\name{drawPie}
\alias{drawPie}
\title{
Draw a pie chart of row counts from a given category.
}
\description{
Takes the data frame generated by \code{getFestivalData()} and a column
name to use for aggregation, and draws a pie chart illustrating the
relative numbers of data frame rows in each category. Note that the
default output from \code{getFestivalData()} lists dip measurements by
cask; to get counts of products per category you will need to first
aggregate the data frame as shown in the example.
}
\usage{
drawPie(cp, colname, cols = 1:9, radius = 0.8, ...)
}
